Previous Save Backup¶{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Calibri;}{\f1\fnil\fcharset0 Arial;}}{&1310}{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}{&1310}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\lang9\f0\fs22 Ok two things - {&1310}\par One - {&1310}\par In the library yesterday an old man sat at a table attempting to write in a musical greeting card.  Each time he opened it it emitted a loud recorded scream - it was obnoxious as hell and I would have been upset if he wasn’t so obviously trying to keep the card from yelling - he folded the cover, opened it quickly, seemingly oblivious to the fact that the card would only scream once and that instead of protecting us he was simply blasting us with the scream over and over and over again.{&1310}\par Two - {&1310}\par The teddy bear I found on your bed.  I made a joke about it but I didn’t know it was from back then.  You told me the arms were shaped so they would hug you around the neck, that that made it a special bear, one that warranted a place on your bed for thirteen years.  I pictured you lying there, twelve years old, fuzzy arms cradling your small frame.  Do they give you a special bear in a situation like that?  One that hugs back?  I waited till you nodded off and felt it and  - they're just regular arms, Kate.  I bet you don't know that's the most vulnerable thing you've ever showed me.  And that seeing it in your bed, at twenty five, was the weakest you've ever been in front of me.{&1310}\par One - {&1310}\par The old woman the card was for.  The envelope was barely sealed when she appeared from behind a row of books and man extended it, shaking and nervous.{&1310}\par  "It's wonderful."{&1310}\par "Really? Do you mean it?"   His words begged, they yearned.{&1310}\par \tab "Yes, absolutely.  Another year older and - oh this is the best one I've seen.”{&1310}\par \tab It was a fucking card.  One that screamed when you opened it.  I don't know if the woman was just being overly nice or if maybe she too was going senile or maybe that's just the way things get to be, when you're older and you know that a feeling is more important than an opinion.{&1310}\par Two - {&1310}\par I don't know how the two stories relate really but I can't stop thinking about them in tandem - the old man with the quivering wrist trying to squeeze his thoughts onto a surface that won’t stop screaming, and that bear on your bed that I pushed out of the way to lay beside you.  I know its not quite the same but, I like it when its my arms around your neck, when you bury your face so deep in my chest that your breath gets my shirt moist.  I want to be the thing you drape around your neck on those few occasions that you cry, because though you've never let me see it, I know they exist.  I want to be your comfort, I want to be your artificial safety cause god KNOWS I can't protect you from any of the things hurting you now any more than a stuffed bear could of protected you from the things that were hurting you then.  But that's not the point.{&1310}\par One - {&1310}\par I don’t know what he wrote in the card, but I know it's the way I feel.  {&1310}\par {&1310}\par \pard\sl0\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\f1 {&1310}\par }{&1310}
